    "title": "Immediate Requirement Production Engineer at Adhesives & Allied Products",
    "description": "We at Adhesives & Allied Products are looking for an experienced Production Engineer based out of Varanasi. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Adhesives & Allied Products:\nAdhesives & Allied Products is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Manage raw material procurement and inventory levels\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Adhesives & Allied Products!",
